To set up your development environment, follow the steps outlined below. This will ensure you have a robust and productive workspace for coding, debugging, version control, and collaboration.
1. Select Your Operating System (OS)
Download and Install Windows 11
•	Go to the Windows 11 download page.
•	Follow the instructions to download and install Windows 11.
 
2. Install a Text Editor or Integrated Development Environment (IDE)
Download and Install Visual Studio Code
•	Go to the Visual Studio Code download page.
•	Download the installer for your operating system.
•	Run the installer and follow the prompts to install Visual Studio Code.
 
3. Set Up Version Control System
Install Git
•	Go to the Git download page.
•	Download and install Git for your operating system.
•	Open Git Bash and configure your Git settings:
sh
Copy code
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"
Create a GitHub Account
•	Go to GitHub and sign up for an account.
Initialize a Git Repository
•	Open Git Bash.
•	Navigate to your project directory:
sh
Copy code
cd path/to/your/project
•	Initialize a Git repository:
sh
Copy code
git init
•	Create a .gitignore file and make your first commit:
sh
Copy code
echo "node_modules/" >> .gitignore
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
•	Push your code to GitHub:
sh
Copy code
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/your-repository.git
git push -u origin master
4. Install Necessary Programming Languages and Runtimes
Install Python
•	Go to the Python download page.
•	Download and install the latest version of Python.
 
5. Install Package Managers
Install pip
•	Pip is included with Python. To ensure it is installed, run:
sh
Copy code
python -m ensurepip --upgrade
6. Configure a Database (MySQL)
Download and Install MySQL
•	Go to the MySQL download page.
•	Download and install the MySQL installer.
•	Follow the setup instructions to configure MySQL.
 
7. Set Up Development Environments and Virtualization (Optional)
Install Docker
•	Go to the Docker download page.
•	Download and install Docker Desktop.
8. Explore Extensions and Plugins
Visual Studio Code Extensions
•	Open Visual Studio Code.
•	Go to the Extensions view by clicking the Extensions icon in the Sidebar or pressing Ctrl+Shift+X.
•	Search for and install useful extensions, such as:
o	Python
o	GitLens
o	Prettier - Code formatter
o	Docker
 
9. Document Your Setup
Document the Setup Process
Create a document detailing the setup process with step-by-step instructions and screenshots. Include any configurations, customizations, or troubleshooting steps encountered during the process.
10. Reflection on Challenges Faced
Write a reflection on the challenges faced during setup and the strategies employed to overcome them.


Deliverables
1.	Document: A comprehensive document outlining the setup process.
2.	GitHub Repository: A sample project initialized with Git and necessary configuration files (e.g., .gitignore).
3.	Reflection: A reflection on the challenges faced and strategies employed to overcome the

